HEADWORD: Short-jointed
<hw>Short"-joint`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having short
intervals between the joints; -- said of a plant or an animal,
especially of a horse whose pastern is too short.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Short-lived</ent>⟦br⟧
